headlines.description: Landry Shamut scored 19 points, and No. 19 Wichita State ended the nation's longest home-court winning streak, beating No. 5 Cincinnati 76-72 on Sunday to leave the American Athletic Conference race wide-open.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 19 Wichita State upends No. 5 Cincinnati 76-72

video.headline: Wichita State snaps Cincinnati's home win streak

headlines.description: Carsen Edwards scored 27 points to lead sixth-ranked Purdue to a 76-73 victory over Penn State on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 27, 6th-ranked Purdue tops Penn State 76-73

video.headline: Purdue holds on against Penn State

headlines.description: Jordan Poole scored 12 of his 15 points in the first half to help No. 22 Michigan take the lead and it never trailed in the second half of a 74-62 win over No. 8 Ohio State on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 22 Michigan tops No. 8 Ohio St 74-62, helps other rival

video.headline: Michigan downs Ohio State for third straight win

headlines.description: Gary Trent Jr. hit three foul shots with 1:31 left to put No. 12 Duke ahead for good and the Blue Devils, again playing without injured star Marvin Bagley III, beat No. 11 Clemson 66-57 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent leads No. 12 Duke to 66-57 win over No. 11 Clemson

headlines.description: Desi Rodriguez scored a career-high 33 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Seton Hall to an 82-77 victory over DePaul on Sunday as the Pirates snapped a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rodriguez scores career-high 33 in Seton Hall's 82-77 win

headlines.description: Jairus Lyles scored 18 of his 22 points in the second half and UMBC rallied from a 12-point deficit to beat Albany 68-60 on Sunday, snapping an eight-game losing streak to the Great Danes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyles leads 2nd-half charge in UMBC's 68-60 win over Albany

headlines.description: Jahad Thomas scored 22 points and UMass Lowell scored its last 10 points from the foul line and beat Binghamton 74-69 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: UMass Lowell seals it at foul line to beat Binghamton 74-69

headlines.description: Austin Tilghman scored 24 points and sank four free throws at the end of the third overtime to lift Monmouth over Siena 93-89 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tilghman saves Monmouth in 93-89 3OT thriller over Siena

video.headline: Siena player mistakenly intentionally fouls in tie game

headlines.description: Dimencio Vaughn scored 22 points with nine rebounds and Jordan Allen added three 3-pointers and 19 points as Rider defeated Canisius 83-82 on Sunday in a matchup of the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference's top teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rider edges Canisius 83-82 for its 10th straight victory

headlines.description: Jason Dunne made five 3-pointers and scored 26 points and Hartford ended Vermont's nation-best 15-game winning streak with a 69-68 victory on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hartford ends Vermont's nation-best 15-game win streak 69-68

headlines.description: UC Iroegbu hit three 3-pointers and scored 17 points and Stony Brook defeated New Hampshire 72-63 on Sunday to split the season series and join the Wildcats in fifth place in the America East Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iroegbu leads Stony Brook past New Hampshire 72-63

headlines.description: Will Rayman scored 15 points to help Colgate beat Loyola (Md.) 68-47 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colgate beats Loyola (Md.) 68-47

headlines.description: Chris Clemons scored 24 of his 26 points in the second half, Marcus Burk added 19 points and the pair each made four of Campbell 15 3-pointers in a 79-69 victory over Liberty on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemons scores 24 of 26 in 2nd half, Campbell beats Liberty

headlines.description: Jordan Whitehead scored 12 points and High Point beat Gardner-Webb 66-65 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: High Point beats Gardner-Webb 66-65

headlines.description: Josh Ferguson had 13 points and 13 rebounds to lead a balanced attack and Winthrop defeated Longwood 79-64 on Sunday to set up a Big South showdown with UNC Asheville next week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Winthrop's balance sinks Longwood 79-64

headlines.description: Jalen Adams scored 26 points and Connecticut held on to beat East Carolina 84-80 on Sunday despite giving up a triple-double to the Pirates' Isaac Fleming.
headlines.shortLinkText: UConn beats ECU 84-80 despite Fleming's triple-double

headlines.description: Martins Igbanu scored 14 of his 16 points in the second half and Tulsa beat South Florida 73-61 on Sunday for the Golden Hurricane's fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Igbanu leads second-half surge in Tulsa's 73-61 victory

headlines.description: Joe Rosga scored 13 points with 10 rebounds, Jake Krafka made three free throws at the end and Denver beat Oral Roberts 66-65 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Denver holds Oral Roberts down the stretch for 66-65 win

headlines.description: Donald Hicks scored 15 points on a career-high tying five 3-pointers and Christian Bradford had 13 points to help Radford beat Presbyterian 74-68 in overtime on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hicks hits 5 3s, Radford beats Presbyterian 74-68 in OT

headlines.description: Leron Black scored a career-high 28 points and snagged seven rebounds, to help Illinois outlast Nebraska for a 72-66 victory on Sunday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Black's career-high 28 pushes Illinois past Nebraska 72-66

headlines.description: Corey Davis Jr. scored 20 points, Devin Davis had a double-double and Houston rolled to its fifth straight victory with an 80-59 win against Temple on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Houston leads start to finish in 80-59 rout over Temple

headlines.description: Marques Townes scored 22 points and Clayton Custer added four 3-pointers and 17 points as Loyola-Chicago claimed at least a share of its first Missouri Valley Conference regular-season championship Sunday with a 76-66 victory over Evansville.
headlines.shortLinkText: Loyola-Chicago clinches at least share of MVC title

headlines.description: Reed Timmer completed a 4-point play with 1.8 seconds left in the game to cap a 20-point outing in Drake's 67-63 win over Missouri State on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timmer's 4-point play at buzzer lifts Drake

headlines.description: MaCio Teague and Ahmad Thomas combined to shoot 9 of 15 from 3-point range and scored 47 points to help UNC Asheville beat Charleston Southern 85-80 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNC Asheville beats Charleston Southern 85-80 in OT

headlines.description: PJ Savoy scored 18 points, M.J. Walker and Phil Cofer added 14 apiece and Florida State rallied in the second half to defeat Pittsburgh 88-75 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida State rallies in second half to defeat Pittsburgh

headlines.description: Daejon Davis scored 22 points before fouling out, Dorian Pickens made two free throws with 8.7 seconds remaining and Stanford overcame an erratic second half to beat California 77-73 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford holds off late surge to beat California 77-73

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma freshman Trae Young, the national leader in scoring at 29 PPG, is shooting 4 for 27 from 3-point range in the Sooners' past three games, all losses. Young had the attention of Allen Fieldhouse throughout OU warmups. He scored 26 on 7-of-9 shooting in Oklahoma's win last month over Kansas.

nowFeed.headline: Will Oklahoma, which has lost five straight, try to rekindle some of its earlier form by going back to the Hack-a-Dok strategy that helped it beat Kansas 85-80 on Jan. 23? The Sooners intentionally fouled 7-foot Kansas center Udoka Azubuike several times in the win as he shot 1 of 7 from the line. Azubuike has slightly improved his free-throw shooting over the past month. He was at 41 percent before the debacle in Norman; he's now shooting 44.7 percent.

nowFeed.headline: Another Big Monday at tap at Allen Fieldhouse, where No. 8 Kansas faces slumping Oklahoma and star freshman Trae Young tonight. The Jayhawks are also home next Monday against Texas, sandwiched around a visit Saturday to Texas Tech, which will loom extremely large in Kansas' bid to win at least a share of its 14th straight Big 12 title. Coach Bill Self is 24-0 at home on Big Monday.

nowFeed.headline: Spoke with E.J Montgomery who currently sits at no.16 in the ESPN 100. He has visited Duke and North Carolina unofficially and plans to go back to both for official visits. Kentucky is up next for an official visit on February 24th. He and is family are deciding on a fourth visit between Georgetown and Wake Forest. At 6'10" Montgomery  possesses a 7'2" wing span with a soft mid-range touch.  He is playing with more assertiveness and that has translated to his rebounding numbers. The bottom line is he has made steady progress over his career with plenty of growth left in his game.

nowFeed.headline: Former Espn 100 Hasahn French earns co-Rookie of the Week honors at Saint Louis. French has set a single-season freshman record for blocks in a season with 52. The school record for blocked shots in a season across all classes is 73, set by Willie Reed in the 2009-10 season.  Saint Louis takes on Dayton tomorrow night 9pm on ESPNU.
